<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.260523>
    dc:description "FIGURE 33. Bryopesanser pesanseris (Smitt, 1873): A, portion of colony; B, small unbleached colony, showing ‘ duckfoot’ avicularian mandibles; C, distal end of zooid with ooecium; D, close-up of orifice, showing spines and developing ooecium; E, uncleaned zooid showing avicularian mandibles and zooid operculum; F, close up of base of mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 1 mm; C, 0.3 mm; D, E, 0.1 mm; F, 0.05 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/260523/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

